article.story: BANGOR, Maine -- — Peter Filipovity had 13 points in Maine's 62-56 victory against UMBC on Thursday night. Filipovity added 11 rebounds for the Black Bears (12-15, 4-8 America East Conference). Kellen Tynes scored 12 points while going 4 of 11 and 4 of 7 from the free throw line. Kristians Feierbergs finished 3 of 5 from 3-point range to finish with 11 points. The Retrievers (9-19, 4-9) were led by Dion Brown, who posted 17 points, 14 rebounds and five assists. Marcus Banks added 16 points for UMBC. In addition, Max Lorca-Lloyd had eight points and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
